<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900905-0021</DOCNO><DOCID>900905-0021.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Suffield Financial   Is Facing Lawsuit   by Officers of Unit</HL><DATE>09/05/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   SFCP</CO><IN>EASTERN U.S. BANKS (BAE)BANKS (BNK)</IN><LP>   SUFFIELD, Conn. -- Suffield Financial Corp. said thepresident and chief executive officer of its Coastal SavingsBank unit filed suit against Suffield Financial in MaineSuperior Court for attempting to dismiss them.   Suffield Financial, a bank holding company, voted in lateJuly to negotiate, by mutual consent, the termination ofRichard Paige, the chief executive, and James McKay, thepresident, of Coastal Savings.</LP><TEXT>   Unsuccessful in its negotiations, Suffield then voted toremove the directors of Coastal Bancorp, a subsidiary ofSuffield Financial and parent of Coastal Savings, and replacethem with new directors. The new Coastal Bancorp board hasnow called a shareholders meeting in order to consider theremoval of the directors of Coastal Savings.   Suffield said it took such action because &quot;a change inCoastal's management would enhance the future profitabilityof Coastal Savings.&quot; While Coastal Savings is &quot;financiallysound,&quot; the bank hasn't been as profitable as it could be,said Suffield Financial.   Messrs. Paige and McKay, who are joined in their suit bycertain other directors of Coastal Savings, said in theirsuit that the actions of Suffield Financial are &quot;illegal andinvalid.&quot;   Suffield has removed the lawsuit to the U.S. DistrictCourt in Maine.</TEXT></DOC>